L√© Vibe ‚Äî quick steps after apt install
=======================================

1. Install a Code - OSS‚Äìcompatible editor (e.g. VSCodium at /usr/bin/codium). Package recommends: codium.

**`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`:** If your editor binary is not the default, set **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** to a full path or a command on **`PATH`** before **`lvibe`**. When you build the L√© Vibe IDE from **`editor/`** in the monorepo, point **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** at that binary (see **`editor/README.md`** in the source tree). This **`le-vibe`** package does not install the IDE binary by itself.

**Default editor when `LE_VIBE_EDITOR` is unset (14.g):** the launcher uses the same order as **`le_vibe.launcher._default_editor`** in **`le-vibe/le_vibe/launcher.py`**: **`$LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** if set; else **`/usr/bin/le-vibe-ide`** if that path exists and is executable; else **`/usr/bin/codium`** if executable; else the command **`codium`** on **`PATH`**. **`debian/control`** **`Recommends: codium`** covers the usual case until a future **`le-vibe-ide`** package exists.

**Future `le-vibe-ide` package (14.g):** When a separate Debian package installs a branded binary (e.g. **`/usr/bin/le-vibe-ide`**), the stack is expected to **`Recommends:`** or **`Suggests:`** that package and document the default **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** story (launcher resolution order vs **`/etc/profile.d/`**‚Äîsee **`editor/BUILD.md`** *14.g*). That package is **not** built from this source tree yet; until it exists, keep using **`codium`** or an explicit **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`**.

2. Run the launcher once so first-run can install Ollama (if needed), pull a model, and write configs under ~/.config/le-vibe/:
     lvibe
   (Compatibility: `le-vibe` is the same entrypoint.)

3. Wire Continue in one step (as your normal user, not root):
     le-vibe-setup-continue
   Exit codes are documented in the main README (0 ok; 1 need first-run; 2 sync; 3 extension; 4 no editor).

4. Open the editor, confirm Continue uses apiBase http://127.0.0.1:11435 (managed Ollama).

IDE sources in a clone (developers)
------------------------------------
End users who only install this **`.deb`** do not need the monorepo. If you **do** have a full clone with **`editor/vscodium`** initialized (**`git submodule update --init --recursive`**), run **`./editor/smoke.sh`** from the repository root to exercise the same **H6** layout and script checks as **`build-le-vibe-ide.yml`** / **`build-linux.yml`** (no Electron compile ‚Äî the latter is a manual **`workflow_dispatch`** alias). On **GitHub Actions**, **`build-le-vibe-ide`** uploads pre-binary **`ide-ci-metadata.txt`** (**`le_vibe_editor_docs`**) with **`upload-artifact`** **`retention-days`**, declares workflow **`permissions:`** **`contents: read`**, **`actions: write`** (checkout + artifact upload), and the job **Summary** includes **Pre-binary artifact** / **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** (see **`editor/BUILD.md`** *CI*, **`editor/VENDORING.md`**). See **`editor/README.md`** and **`docs/ci-qa-hardening.md`** (*IDE smoke*).

Model lock (inspectable)
------------------------
Hardware tiering picks a **concrete** Ollama model tag for this machine. It is stored as:
  ~/.config/le-vibe/locked-model.json
together with `model-decision.json` and `continue-config.yaml`. The product does **not** persist a vague AUTODETECT-only lock when a real tag is known.

Workspace `.lvibe/`
-------------------
When you open a folder (e.g. `lvibe .`), the launcher asks for **workspace memory** consent on first use (**`PRODUCT_SPEC` ¬ß5**). If you **accept**, it prepares **`.lvibe/`** at the project root, appends **`.lvibe/`** to `.gitignore` when a `.gitignore` already exists, and adds small agent-oriented files for token-efficient local memory. If you **decline**, no **`.lvibe/`** folder is created.

Authority (clone the upstream repository)
------------------------------------------
Must-ship product requirements: **`docs/PRODUCT_SPEC.md`**. Maintainer index (Roadmap **H1‚ÄìH8**): **`docs/README.md`**. Formal roster of orchestration docs: **`PRODUCT_SPEC` ¬ß9** (*Relationship to existing specs*). **E1 / acceptance:** **`docs/PRODUCT_SPEC_SECTION8_EVIDENCE.md`** ‚Äî maps **`le-vibe/tests/`** to ¬ß5‚Äì¬ß10 (clone the upstream tree to run **`pytest`**). Full **E1** roster ‚Äî project root **`README.md`** (*Tests* / **E1 mapping**); **`docs/spec-phase2.md` ¬ß14** *Honesty vs CI*. **Privacy / reporting:** **`docs/privacy-and-telemetry.md`** (*E1 contract tests* row); **`SECURITY.md`** (**`Related docs`** lists **`docs/README`** *Product surface* ‚Äî **H8** **`.github/`** ‚Äî **`ci.yml`**, **`dependabot.yml`**, **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`** + **`config.yml`** **`#` H8** + **`privacy-and-telemetry`** *E1*; and optional **`docs/rag/le-vibe-phase2-chunks.md`** ‚Äî *RAG / embeddings*, **`spec-phase2.md` ¬ß14*, non-canonical).

**Phase 2 scope (this `.deb` vs fork / Flatpak):** In an upstream clone, read **`docs/spec-phase2.md` ¬ß14** ‚Äî this source package ships launcher + bootstrap + configs; a **branded editor-only** binary (**H6**) and **in-repo** Flatpak/AppImage (**H7**) are **not** claimed from this repository alone.

See /usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README and LICENSE. Upstream README: project repository.
